{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Our initial experiments investigate the performance capabilities of LLMs to detect threats, a trait which traditional more lightweight ML solutions have already been proven to possess with near perfection [4].",
    "We will evaluate our model variants on the NF-UNSW-NB15-v2 and NF-CSE-CIC-IDS2018-v2 datasets [5].",
    "Finally, we investigate the capacity to explain the detection of threats and their computational cost of inference to fuel a discussion on the advantages and drawbacks of using LLMs for NIDS versus more lightweight solutions incorporating LLMs as a complementary solution to existing NIDS.",
    "Our findings aim to provide a first exploratory evaluation of LLMs in the context of NIDS, offering insights into potential future research directions and use cases.",
    "We do not aim for a comprehensive benchmark of models and parameters of LLMs for detecting malicious NetFlows."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
